  "prompt": "How do I stop myself from thinking about death all the time?",
  "response": "Dealing with constant thoughts about death can be challenging. Here are some strategies that might help:\n\n1. Seek professional help\n- Talk to a therapist or counselor who can help you address underlying anxiety or depression\n- Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) can be particularly effective\n\n2. Practice mindfulness and meditation\n- Focus on the present moment\n- Learn techniques to redirect intrusive thoughts\n- Use apps like Headspace or Calm for guided meditation\n\n3. Engage in meaningful activities\n- Pursue hobbies and interests\n- Volunteer or help others\n- Set personal goals and work towards them\n\n4. Exercise and maintain physical health\n- Regular physical activity can reduce anxiety\n- Boost endorphins and improve mental well-being\n\n5. Connect with others\n- Share your feelings with trusted friends or family\n- Join support groups\n- Build strong social connections\n\n6. Practice self-care\n- Get enough sleep\n- Eat a balanced diet\n- Limit caffeine and alcohol\n\n7. Challenge negative thoughts\n- Recognize when thoughts become irrational\n- Use positive self-talk\n- Develop coping strategies\n\n8. Consider medication\n- Consult a psychiatrist about potential anxiety or depression treatments\n\nRemember, persistent thoughts about death might indicate an underlying mental health issue, so professional help is recommended.",
